```cpp
#include <hexi/hexi.h>
#include <vector>
#include <string>
#include <cstdint>

struct NetworkPacket {
    uint32_t packet_id;
    std::string username;
    std::vector<uint32_t> scores;
    std::string metadata;

    void serialise(auto& stream) {
        // Write packet_id using operator<<
        stream << packet_id;

        // Write username with prefix using prefixed adaptor
        stream << hexi::prefixed(username);

        // Write scores count first, then use operator<< which internally calls write_container
        stream << hexi::prefixed(scores);

        // Write metadata as null-terminated string using null_terminated adaptor
        stream << hexi::null_terminated(metadata);
    }
};

std::vector<uint8_t> serialize_packet(const NetworkPacket& packet) {
    // Create a buffer_adaptor for the destination buffer
    std::vector<uint8_t> buffer;
    hexi::buffer_adaptor<std::vector<uint8_t>> adaptor(buffer);

    // Create a binary_stream with the buffer_adaptor
    hexi::binary_stream<decltype(adaptor)> stream(adaptor);

    // Call the packet's serialise method on the stream
    packet.serialise(stream);

    // Return the buffer containing the serialized data
    return buffer;
}
```

## Key Implementation Points:

1. **`serialise` method implementation**:
   - Uses `operator<<` for `packet_id` (POD type)
   - Uses `hexi::prefixed` adaptor for `username` (length-prefixed string)
   - Uses `hexi::prefixed` adaptor for `scores` (length-prefixed container)
   - Uses `hexi::null_terminated` adaptor for `metadata` (null-terminated string)

2. **`serialize_packet` function**:
   - Creates `std::vector<uint8_t>` as the destination buffer
   - Creates `hexi::buffer_adaptor` wrapping the vector
   - Creates `hexi::binary_stream` with the adaptor
   - Calls `packet.serialise(stream)` to perform serialization
   - Returns the populated buffer

3. **Proper use of Hexi library components**:
   - Correctly uses the adaptors (`prefixed`, `null_terminated`) as specified
   - Follows the serialization pattern shown in the reference materials
   - Maintains proper type safety and resource management

